com.fincons.mqtt.client.service

Class MessageSubscribeService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fincons.mqtt.client.service.MessageSubscribeService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.eclipse.paho.client.mqttv3.MqttCallback

    public class MessageSubscribeService
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.eclipse.paho.client.mqttv3.MqttCallback
    This class defines a consumer of a specific set of events dispatched by another MQTT client on a specific topic. The actual processing of the events is performed by the registered instances of MqttCallback. See the class SimpleMqttCallback for more details about the subscriber business logic.
    Author:
    leonardo.straniero
    See Also:
    SimpleMqttCallback

      • messageArrived

        public void messageArrived(java.lang.String topic,
                           org.eclipse.paho.client.mqttv3.MqttMessage message)
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        This method defines the business logic implemented in the client subscriber when a new message is delivered to the topic selected. N.B. To permit the customization of the subscriber business logic, is preferable to register a MqttCallback externally (e.g. during the use of the library, at client side). For more details about the subscriber business logic please see the class SimpleMqttCallback.
        Specified by:
        messageArrived in interface org.eclipse.paho.client.mqttv3.MqttCallback
